{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"drum-ruler-suit","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. A ticket bound to a Jira issue is detached from its parent locally: `rebar edit <id> --parent=null` (parent_id → None).\n2. `show <id>` confirms parent_id is empty immediately.\n3. Within minutes the reconcile-bridge cron (~3-min) re-parents the ticket back to its old epic.\n\n**Expected:** the detach sticks; Jira's epic-link is cleared to match local.\n**Actual:** the detach is silently reverted every reconcile pass (observed on super-plant-liver + toy-kink-ire reverting to epic peak-fir-hilt).\n\n## Root Cause (proven via /joe-debug)\n\nThe Jira reconciler had an **asymmetric** parent sync:\n- **Outbound never emitted a parent CLEAR.** `outbound_differ._map_local_to_jira_fields` only set `result['parent']` when local parent_id was truthy (outbound_differ.py:364). On a detach (parent_id None), no parent field was mapped, so the field-diff loop's parent branch never ran and outbound emitted nothing, leaving Jira's stale epic-link.\n- **Inbound unconditionally re-applied it.** `inbound_differ._diff_jira_vs_local` (inbound_differ.py:307-316) re-emitted `parent_id=<epic>` whenever Jira's resolved parent != local parent_id. The same-pass suppression (_OUTBOUND_TO_INBOUND_FIELD) only fires when outbound emits a parent mutation, which on a detach it never did.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Outbound differ emits a parent CLEAR (parent: None) when a ticket is detached locally but its Jira snapshot still carries a parent (stale epic-link).\n- [ ] The outbound applier (batch_dispatch.update_one) routes the CLEAR through set_parent(key, None) to clear the Jira epic-link.\n- [ ] A never-parented bound ticket (local None, Jira None) emits NO parent mutation (no churn the other direction).\n- [ ] The same-pass inbound suppression prevents the inbound re-parent so the detach converges.\n- [ ] A regression test asserts the outbound differ emits the CLEAR for a detached-but-Jira-parented ticket (held-out RED then GREEN).","id":"7f42-a88b-ec1a-4e8b","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Parent-detach churn: reconciler asymmetric parent sync reverts local detaches"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782532109163060001,"uuid":"5220e1bc-afb1-4968-ba06-f5da1f30ac4b"}